OL,6,F"The shooting was unnecessary and it
OL,7,Fwas gratuitous and it was carried out,
OL,8,Fgiven the weapon involved, with an
OL,9,Fintent to kill and, in any event, at
OL,10,Fthe least with an intent to cause
OL,11,Freally serious harm."
OL,13,FMr Mably went on to set the scene of
OL,14,Fthe shootings, noting that those shot
OL,15,Fwere mostly struck to the side or the
OL,16,Fback, describing scared people who
OL,17,Fwere running away.
OL,19,F"These soldiers lost control of
OL,20,Fthemselves," he said, describing their
OL,21,Fbehaviour as "unprofessional".
