OL,6,F"We will shortly occupy a courtroom
OL,7,Fvery proudly with our heads held high
OL,8,Fand in the knowledge that, regardless
OL,9,Fof the ultimate outcome, that we are
OL,10,Fon the right side of history.
OL,12,F"A matter of a few metres away from us
OL,13,Fin the courtroom will sit Soldier F,
OL,14,Fcowering behind a curtain, waiting to
OL,15,Fgo on trial for two counts of murder
OL,16,Fand five counts of attempted murder."
OL,18,FMr McKinney added: "Today, we place
OL,19,Four trust in the hands of the Public
OL,20,FProsecution Service to finish the job.
