OL,6,FIn 2019, Northern Ireland's Public
OL,7,FProsecution Service (PPS) announced
OL,8,Fthat one former paratrooper, Soldier
OL,9,FF, would face prosecution for two
OL,10,Fmurders and five counts of attempted
OL,11,Fmurder.
OL,13,FHowever, two years later, the PPS
OL,14,Fhalted the prosecution, citing
OL,15,Fconcerns the case could collapse if it
OL,16,Fwent to trial.
OL,18,FThat move followed the collapse of a
OL,19,Fdifferent legacy trial of two other
OL,20,Fveterans accused of murder during the
OL,21,FTroubles.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G16/19
